reviews.text: Such a nice place,  with great staff. A lot of intresting things,  plus live animals. My son's favorite was the live bees and Boris the turtle! A very cute, local museum. A good place to spead with your kids on a school holiday.  It was cold when we went, but we will definitely be back with a packed lunch to eat outside.

The Google description starts with "large" ... well, this one is hardly large. I really took my time and spent about an hour here. Kids would probably blow through in 30 minutes. It's not only natural history, there are some historic displays of the area such as weaving, chuck wagons, etc. Good for a nice, short, educational visit.

We love taking our nieces and family members to the museum!!

The staff is friendly, the exhibits constantly change and the exhibit openings are very interesting and the speakers both educational and interesting!!

We highly recommend going and experiencing and supporting the museum of natural history.

Doug and Cheryl Pederson
Fun small museum, great interactive animal area for kids (and adults!).

Smallest "museum" I believe I've ever been too. There was a section that was covered for remodel,  but even with it open it wouldn't be much better.  What the heck is the rest of the huge building for?  $22 for a family of 5 and we're we're in and out in 30 min. Disappointed :(

My wife and I took my daughter on a campus visit this weekend.  My daughter loved the school and has the school on her list along with Colorado State among others.

I on the other hand was somewhat disappointed.  It was just not a very welcoming experience.  The students that were providing the various tours were polite enough but it wasn’t really a,” Welcome to aTm! We are so glad that you’re considering us!”.  Instead it was, “Howdy, consider yourself fortunate enough if you are accepted.”. 

I’ve been to plenty of campuses to include CU (Boulder), UT (Austin), Baylor (Waco), UCSB (Santa Barbara), etc.  Some campus visits required a fee but they also provided meals, parking and swag.  They gave you the feeling of belonging and you wanted to enroll there.  

aTm on the other hand wanted to show how big they were, how much everything would cost and if you wanted to visit various areas of the campus, they made a profit by charging you parking at every opportunity.  

I was slightly surprised as you would think the 3rd largest university in the country would have the assets to provide parking waivers or a day pass for visiting parents.

The amenities and facilities were very nice and what you would expect from a top tier university.  The campus was clean and various construction was occurring to indicate growth.

We were slightly surprised that the campus was beginning to feel cramped as it appears they had surrounding acreage to expand.  

With that being said, the nursing school did seem to be a good distance from the main campus.  So they might be working on this type of expansion.

As a helpful suggestion, offer parking passes to registered visitors (even if they have to pay for it). Along with google links to the various schools of interest for visitors.  As Google maps has not been updated in some time and some of the college of study were outdated.  (This might be something the computer science students could work on?)
I loved my time at A&M. There’s nothing like an Aggie football game

Texas A&M University, referred to as TAMU. Founded in 1876, the school is located in Card City, Texas, USA, a member of the top 100 universities in the world, and the American Association of Universities (AAU), the leading research university alliance in North America. The sixth largest public university in the United States has a high academic achievement and teaching standards.
Texas A&M University has the nation's top engineering school and is known worldwide. 2018 USNEWS National Engineering Institute ranked 12th among them: 2nd in petroleum engineering, 3rd in biological and agricultural engineering, 3rd in nuclear engineering, 7th in aerospace engineering, 13th in industrial and systems engineering, civil engineering 15th, mechanical engineering 16th, computer science 17th, the rest of the engineering profession is also among the best.
Texas A&M University's research in basic sciences is also particularly remarkable. Many Nobel laureates have worked or studied here: organic chemistry master Derek Barton has worked here for twelve years and has become a conformational analysis and The main founder of free radical chemistry; Jack Kirby, the father of integrated circuits, is a Distinguished Professor of the School of Electrical Engineering. The famous JK proactor is named after him; Dudley Herschbach et al. The chemical element reaction system won the 1986 Nobel Prize in Chemistry. In addition, TAMU is known for its cutting-edge scientific cloning technology. The first cloned cat and cloned dog in human history are the results of the school.
The school is not only strong in engineering and basic science, but also in the leading position in the emerging fields of accounting, management, and art: 13 in architecture, 15 in accounting, and 20 in urban planning.
In 2018, Texas A&M University ranked 57th in the ARWU North American University of Shanghai Jiaotong University [1], USNEWS ranked 16th in North American universities, ranked 42nd in LeagueTables global universities , CWUR World University ranked 78, North American universities 45 people.
This school scks full of snobby ppl

FISHERY AT BLUE HERON BRIDGE INTENTIONALLY DESTROYED! by Moody Gardens and Texas A&M Blue Heron Bridge, is a world renowned dive site loved by locals This establishment went to collect a sizeable amount of fish and other specimens from one of the best dive sites in Florida, the Blue Heron Bridge. They have destroyed the site Shame on you Texas A&M

Being from New Jersey we don't have big time college football like this, no offence to NJ State University of Rutgers. What a great experience to sit in a stadium of over 100,000 college students, alumni etc. and enjoy a game of SEC football. Stadium is spacious and clean with a student center next door to buy any A & M gear you might want. If you get there early enough be sure to watch the Corps of Cadets marching into he stadium....quite a site! Also check out the final resting place of former "Reveille" dogs, the  official mascot of Texas A & M, a very nice tribute.

Home of the greatest football team in the US
Whoop! Best part of the stadium renovation is the enormous amount of bathrooms. It is also very clean and clean has lots of different food options.

Place is huge! I did not get to go inside and just  experienced the outside. We decided to drive through campus while on a road trip. I must say the campus is very large, but it must be to accommodate so many Aggies!

It's the home of the 12th man, what more is there to say? A great place for a football game! I wish they had some better food selections arranged better throughout the stadium and the bathrooms could be cleaned more. Still a great place though, no bad seats in the House. Wonderful to watch the Aggie football and better the awesome band.

My first experience at an Aggie football game was the 2018 A&M vs LSU 7 OVERTIME game last November!  Imagine, of all the games over the years I COULD of gone to (I've lived in Central Texas since 1990!) my son picked THIS one to take his old man to!  We parked in Bryon - we had read that's what many people do when going to Ag games - finding a place to eat in Bryon was not easy since we didn't really want Mexican or BBQ or pub fare - they have shuttles that run to the stadium and back, so it was easy and a nice experience - the game was a TRIP!  from the cheer leaders to the band to the game itself, it was something we will NEVER forget!  Will be a tough one to top!
Olsen is the home of the true cult of Aggie Sports, baseball. No yell leaders, just some savage chants and a good soundboard. 10/10. It makes me feel so good.
Baseball atmosphere and stadium are great. Burger and hot dogs were cold and tasted like charcoal. I will never buy either at the concession stand again! Gig'em baseball!

Awesome awesome ballpark. Really set up well and the game experience here is second to none. You have to watch a collegiate ballgame here. The students and crowd have so much fun and make it such a memorable experience. The bubbles are fantastic.
We enjoy watching & supporting Texas A&M Basball !!! The food needs improvements not much selection...  Cold hot chocolate for$5.00 doesn't help on cold windy day No coffee either!

Very nicely built! Only complaint would be the seats/rows are too close together. When ppl on the same row have to leave their seat to go to the stairs and they return there's quite a bit of standing and adjusting each time.
We came in for a late dinner not realizing that they were closing soon. The staff still made us cheerfully feel welcomed! The food was excellent! Even better than the past visits there

Good food, pretty good service!! They seem somewhat understaffed. I've been twice in a week, the first time our server disappeared with no communication and then several wait periods with no help. The second time our server was amazing, and got quadruple sat, but made sure we were never waiting for anything. The food itself was pretty good, but the barbacoa tacos were very dry and lukewarm. Will still go back, but looks like there are some  kinks to work out concerning staffing during peak hours..

Place was packed for a Friday afternoon lunch. Service very pleasant but a bit slow as though everyone was on siesta or vacation. Tacos are incredible. No wonder the cute saying on the side of their building.

The food is good & the service is good but I have to say the lack of actions by the owner, manager or whatever the man happens to be made the experience eating at the restaurant leaving much to be desired. He had several children at the table(young kids of various ages), allowing the kids to run all around the restaurant yelling and screaming, nearly running into wait staff on multiple occasions, al.ost running into our table and others for the first 15 minutes we were there. He and his wife did nothing to stop this. He spent much of his time walking into the back and talking with the wait staff ignoring the situation. If my time and comfort is of no concern to him, I do 't need to give my business to this restaurant. Owner/manager or whoever you are, you need to have a little more respect for customers!!!!!!
What a great place to eat! The food was awesome and the service was even better! Thanks for a great dinner Casa Rod!

I love Freebirds. I've been going for the past 15 years.  Wish they didn't change the recipe for the sauce,  because the hot sauce is NOT HOT AT ALL.  It user top button my lips,  not I'm disappointed.  I know there's another but,  Judy not the same.

Monster is a real monster...full meal n then some,all the food groups, everyone enjoyed the dinner out.
Nice choice if you are a little or if you need a full size monster for your appetite
A must try! The convenience of ordering online and picking up at the window was awesome! I have absolutely no complaints about portions or quality. Customer service was outstanding. Thank you.
Decent price, good food. Drive-thru makes it easy to pick-up. Lately, I always have a good experience here.

Passing through college station ... because of the Austin, TX vibe it has, we stopped. The staff was friendly and very helpful. The food, honestly,  liked it better than Chipotle, it was more authentic and flavorful.

I have gone to this location about a half dozen times. It's the only restaurant directly on the way to my husband's office, and he likes the chicken. But in all the times I have gone to pick up lunch, they have NEVER EVER gotten my order right. I don't like fries, so I ask them to take them out. That's it. I want everything in the box EXCEPT FRIES. But they either leave out other parts if the order, or leave the fries in anyway, which I throw out. I have worked in food service and I have no idea why it's so hard to get right.Today was the last time. I will never be back, no matter how convenient it is.

We had the basic chicken finger basket, and the chicken was perfectly cooked, lightly-battered and moist. The fries were also very good and the signature dipping sauce spicy, but not too. They do not make their own potato salad, but it is excellent. The Texas toast could have been a bit more brown, but that's down to my personal taste. Oh, and the iced tea was also excellent. The student types who run the restaurant are cordial and fun.

A TAMU tradition, Laynes is the original chicken finger restaurant in town and definitely has the better chicken fingers.  I just wish I got some really good bread with my meal as my wife loves it from the competition.

A local friend of mine recommended this place and I was pretty happy with the food. The chicken sandwhich was pretty filling and I didn't even get the fries. Great toast and fried chicken combo. Apparently the off menu item to get is the club: chicken sandwhich with bacon.

Excellent fried chicken, their tenders are juicy and the breading is fresh and crisp. Their dipping sauce beats all others, and the fries and toast that come with the meal are pretty good to. Highly reccomend after a long night out on the town.

This is a nice place to go for upscale cuisine in a casually elegant setting downtown. The food was better when Peter and Tara Madden owned and operated it,  but it's still pretty good. I would still probably prefer it over Cafe Excel or Christopher's.

We last ate at Madden's in May and it was a very good meal and experience. Tonight, the appetizer ('beginnings') was bland, two of our party's three entrees were 'meh' but not what we expect from Madden's. Tim, our server, was the best part of the experience.

Great ambiance, always great food. Wines are pricey, but good...no liquor. 
Service is fair. A good go to place for good dining in downtown Bryan.
I can't imagine not having this place in  Bryan, Texas!

Great locally sourced and owned restaurant, good for date night or business lunch. Menu steadily evolves seasonally but classics like their tomato bisque(best I'll ever have) are available year round. Must hit spot if you live in the BCS area and great spot to bring visiting friends, family and professional aquaintances.
Good place for american food. Entered near ten, it was not crowded. I had a cousin come into town and she asked me to go back here. I can see why they have a lot of good reviews.

Fantastic service.  If you want something a bit more authentic, just ask them.  They have a wide selection and cater not only to those wanting TexMex but also to "friends" who want something a bit more traditional.  One of the few Mexican restaurants in town with a pretty good seafood selection.

One of my favorite places in College Station to eat! The food is some of the best here in the city if you're looking for Tex-Mex. But where Los Cucos shines is the service. I've been going there for years and the waiter (Adrian) who knows me best knows exactly what I want before I even sit down. They treat their customers well and its what makes this restaurant stand out against similar places. I highly recommend it.
Great food, atmosphere and service!!   I don't recall a single item I've had on their menu that I didn't enjoy.  Have eaten here several times with family and friends.

Pretty great food so I have to give them credit there but I've only been twice and got fajitas both times. I only go because a group I'm a part of goes though, otherwise I'm not sure I would have ever gone. The pricing seems way too high for the level of service and the atmosphere that they have put on for us, but again I've only been in a big group setting when service is less likely to be sublime.

Small Mexican chain restaurant. Great atmosphere, simple menu, awesome margaritas. Only slightly overpriced, but well worth it just for the excellent wait staff. I've been coming here for over a decade, and have no intention of ever stopping. Personal recommendation: Verde Enchiladas.

A lovely setting and a fun place to visit. Was not crowded and we visited with several people from the winery including the wind Maker.
Lunch was good and the menu was varied..
We have been here several times over the years and it is always enjoyable.
I have many large events with music and entertainment, dinner and wine tasting as well.

YES! I hope everyone has the same wonderful experience I had with Veritas. From their staff to the venue, everything was so much better that I could have hoped for. Their event staff will work closely with you to make your wedding dreams come true. And the simplistic elegance of the whole property matched my style perfectly. I'm still hearing about how beautiful our venue was, and all credit goes to Veritas. The catering is out of this world good - like really good! Definitely not your average, just so-so wedding food. No, it was AMAZING! Our accommodates for the day were picture perfect, and I could not be happier. Taylor (event manager) is fantastic - she really delivered on all accounts! We loved our wedding day for many reasons, but Veritas is certainly one of the top reasons! I would recommend everyone get married there!
Veritas has a phenomenal wine selection and breathtaking grounds. Sit by the giant cozy fireplace and enjoy a fine cheese plate. Live is good at Veritas.
I really enjoyed the hospitality wonderful ambience the solitude really if that's what you wanted I mean it was just great all the way around..... I do plan on going back.

We stopped in for wine tasting. The staff were friendly and very knowledgeable. Tasting room was cozy & had a large fireplace. Lots of comfortable seating available. Will definitely return & check out the veritas farms next time we visit the area!
